The aide de camp to Edo state governor, Godwin Obaseki caused a stir when he collapsed recently.  The ADC collapsed at the governor’s swearing-in ceremony for a second term on Thursday, November 12. Shortly after he took his oath of office, Governor Obaseki took to the podium to give his speech. It was while he was giving his speech that his ADC collapsed as other security agents rallied round to help him. Watch a video that captured the moment below: Governor Godwin Obaseki's ADC collapsed at his swearing-in ceremony for a second term today November 12. Shortly after he took his oath of office, Governor Obaseki took to the podium to give his speech. It was while he was giving his speech that his ADC collapsed behind him. Other security agents rushed to help him. A post shared by  Lindaikejiblog (@lindaikejiblogofficial) on Nov 12, 2020 at 5:45am PST Source According to SaharaReporters there is a simmering tension in Kebbi State between Governor Saidu Nasamu Dakingari and police officers upset about the governor’s assault of his aide de camp, Mohammed Umar, on Saturday, September 9. Several police sources in the state told a correspondent of SaharaReporters that the assault took place at the Ahmadu… September 19, 2014 In "News" By Joy Odigie Benin -  Gov. Godwin Obaseki of Edo on Monday in Benin swore-in the new Head of Service (HOS) for the state, Mr Isaac Ehiozuwa. The News Agency of Nigeria (NAN) reports that Ehiozuwa, who had been the Accountant-General of the state, took over from Mrs Gladys Idahor,… November 26, 2018 In "Politics" By Sufuyan Ojeifo‎ Many Nigerians, especially Edo indigenes and residents, had patiently waited for the gubernatorial campaign flag off of the All Progressives Party (APC) in Edo State, so as to make some sensible inference and possibly a starter-opinion-projection on the likely candidate to beat in the September 10 election.… July 21, 2016 In "Opinion"